# BooksForge — code ownership and review gates.
#
# Lines later in this file take precedence. The default owner is the
# repository owner; specific paths add additional required reviewers.
#
# See https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default owner for everything in the repo.
*                                          @DipurajThapa

# ── Security-sensitive surfaces ─────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Tauri capability JSONs widen the desktop attack surface. Any change
# here must be reviewed for least-privilege. Adding `shell:`, `http:`,
# or broad `fs:` patterns requires a documented justification in the PR.
# (Audit ref: EXTERNAL_AUDIT_BACKLOG.md #16)
booksforge/apps/desktop/capabilities/**    @DipurajThapa
booksforge/apps/desktop/tauri.conf.json    @DipurajThapa

# CI workflows define what runs on every PR — including the privacy
# invariants tests. Drift here can silently disable enforcement.
.github/workflows/**                       @DipurajThapa
booksforge/.github/workflows/**            @DipurajThapa

# Privacy posture: cross-layer policy. Any new entry to deny.toml's
# bans / licenses block, or any change to the privacy_invariants test,
# must be reviewed against outputs/SECURITY_PRIVACY.md.
booksforge/deny.toml                                                    @DipurajThapa
booksforge/crates/booksforge-orchestrator/tests/privacy_invariants.rs   @DipurajThapa

# IPC contract: changes here ripple to TS via ts-rs codegen. Reviewers
# should verify codegen_drift CI is green and that handwritten TS bindings
# are not introduced.
booksforge/crates/booksforge-ipc/**        @DipurajThapa
booksforge/packages/shared-types/**        @DipurajThapa

# Storage migrations are forward-only at runtime. New SQL files OK;
# edits to existing migration files are NOT.
booksforge/crates/booksforge-storage/migrations/**   @DipurajThapa

# Governance / legal artefacts.
LICENSE                                    @DipurajThapa
SECURITY.md                                @DipurajThapa
CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md                         @DipurajThapa
THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md                    @DipurajThapa
